==Hindi==
===Etymology===
Sanskrit [[अद्बैत]] ''(advaita)'', lit., "not two."

===Noun===
'''अद्बैत''' (advaita) {{m}}

#absolute oneness, one without a second, non duality.
#monism.
#a branch of [[Hinduism]], ''advaita vedanta''.

===Related terms===
*The adjective form is [[अद्बैती]], with an alternate form [[अद्बितीय]].

